2026-04-12: JWT-R for immediate logout support
  - Hybrid approach: SJA (15min access, 7day refresh) + Redis blacklist for immediate logout
  - RS256 asymmetric signing; public keys distributed across API servers enabling SJA validation
  - Eliminates sticky-session routing complexity in distributed systems
  - Redis stores only revoked tokens with TTL; minimal memory overhead vs pure SJA
  - Clock skew < 1min enforced via NTP; refresh token rotation on each use prevents replay attacks
  - HTTPS mandatory; machine-to-machine auth uses separate API keys, never JWT
